            <h3 class="crr-title-h3 text-navy margin-bottom20">5.2. Security</h3>
            <p class="carr-p text-navy text-size22 margin-bottom40">Career.com uses reasonable physical, administrative and technical safeguards to help protect the Collected Information from unauthorized access, use and disclosure. For example, when a customer places an order online through any of Career.com's Websites, the customer's credit card, personal information, employee and related account information is protected through the use of a secure encryption such as the Secure Socket Layer ("SSL") protocol. Career.com also requires that its suppliers protect such information from unauthorized access, use, and disclosure.</p>

            <h3 class="crr-title-h3 text-navy margin-bottom20">5.3. Access Rights and Unsubscribing</h3>

            <h3 class="crr-title-h3 text-navy margin-bottom20">5.3.1. Access Rights</h3>
            <p class="carr-p text-navy text-size22 margin-bottom40">Career.com will provide you with reasonable access to your Personal Information, including in some cases employee information, as well as the ability to review and correct such information. You may access, modify, or remove your Personal Information by contacting <a class="text-blue" href="mailto:privacy@career.com">privacy@career.com</a> or, in some cases, by logging into the Service and making the applicable changes. In order to protect your privacy and security, Career.com will take reasonable steps to verify your identity before granting you access to your Personal Information and may limit or deny access to any information where providing such access would be unreasonable, burdensome, or expensive in the circumstances. Career.com will respond to requests for access within 30 days.</p>

            <h3 class="crr-title-h3 text-navy margin-bottom20">5.3.2. Retention</h3>
